AB  - We consider the model introduced by Hsiao (1979) for analyzing data that are subject to different temporal aggregation. We show that maximum likelihood estimation of the parameters in the model is more complex than Hsiao suggests. Using a simple example we compare the large sample variance of the maximum likelihood estimator with that of the estimator proposed by Hsiao, of the generalized least squares (GLS) estimator and of the OLS estimator applied to aggregate data.
