AB  - The inequality constrained least squares estimator in this paper is from the regression model, y = X1β1 + X2β2 + ε, where both of the regression coefficients are subject to non-negative inequality constraints. The first and second moments of this estimator are derived. The regressors are permitted to be non-orthogonal. A number of conclusions are drawn from comparisons of the inequality constrained least squares estimator with the ordinary least squares and equality constrained least squares estimators.
